verbose_text: These results collectively demonstrate that miR-518a-3p inhibits the basal and receptor initiated activities of the non canonical NF-kappaB pathway and that miR-518a-3p plays a critical role in the negative regulation of the NF-kappaB pathway by manipulating the expression of NIK.
evidence: miR-518a-3p inhibits the basal and receptor-initiated activities of the non-canonical NF-kappaB
